Simone Biles was announced the BET 2020 sport women award winner via a virtual celebration due to the coronavirus pandemic. Biles has 30 Olympic and World Championship medals and is the most decorated American gymnast. — Sportswoman of the year: Simone Biles — Sportsman of the year: LeBron James see other winners, — Best international act: Burna Boy (Nigeria) — Viewer’s choice: Best new international act: Sha Sha (Zimbabwe) — Best actor: Michael B. Jordan — Best movie: “Queen & Slim” — Youngstars award: Marsai Martin — BET HER award: Beyoncé featuring Blue Ivy Carter, Wizkid and Saint JHN, “Brown Skin Girl” — Video director of the year: Teyana Taylor — Album of the year: Roddy Ricch — Humanitarian award: Beyoncé — Dr. Bobby Jones best gospel/inspirational award: Kirk Franklin, “Just for Me” — Best actress: Issa Rae — Video of the year: DJ Khaled featuring Nipsey Hussle and John Legend, “Higher” — Best female R&B/pop artist: Lizzo — Best male R&B/pop artist: Chris Brown — Best female hip-hop artist: Megan Thee Stallion — Best male hip-hop artist: DaBaby — Best new artist: Roddy Ricch — Best group: Migos — Best collaboration: Chris Brown featuring Drake, “No Guidance”